	(51971,200,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'Darti is a male born in 1999 and he belongs to the species of Symphalangus syndactylus (siamang). He was saved from a tradesman who wanted to sell him in Lampung, in the south of the island of Sumatra. Darti is healthy and he is paired with a female called Sunari. They are both in a large cage on Marak island near Padang on the west coast of Sumatra. If you adopt Darti you take part in his process of rehabilitation and the repopulation of his species.','EN'),
