	(52733,435,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<p>Ajun est un m&acirc;le siamang ( <em>Symphalangus Syndactylus</em> ), l&rsquo;une des esp&egrave;ces de gibbons que nous pouvons trouver sur l&rsquo;&icirc;le Sumatera en Indon&eacute;sie.</p>\r\n<p>L&rsquo;estimation de l&rsquo;ann&eacute;e de sa naissance : 1998.</p>\r\n<p>Ajun a &eacute;t&eacute; confisqu&eacute; &agrave; Jakarta, la capitale de l&rsquo;Indonesie.</p>\r\n<p>Il est arriv&eacute; &agrave; Kalaweit Sumatera le 02 decembre 2010.</p>\r\n<p>Le resultat du test sanguin : Ajun est sain.</p>\r\n<p>Notes :</p>\r\n<p>Supayang Conservation Centre et Sanctuaire, Solok, &agrave; l&rsquo;ouest de Sumatera.</p>\r\n<p>Juin 2018</p>\r\n<p>Ajun va bien. Il est actiff et mange bien les fruits.</p>\r\n<p>Janvier 2014</p>\r\n<p>Ajun va bien. Il est actif&nbsp;&agrave; se balancer.</p>\r\n<p>Apr&egrave;s avoir balance, Ajun aime s&rsquo;asseoir et s&rsquo;&eacute;pouiller sur une branche etendue.</p>\r\n<p>Ajun mange bien les fruits et la nourriture suplementaire comme poulet, oeuf dur et lait.</p>\r\n<p>Septembre 2013</p>\r\n<p>Ajun va bien.</p>\r\n<p>Il est actif a se balancer.</p>\r\n<p>Ajun mange bien sa nourriture. il prend et mange toujours en premier les bananes. Apr&egrave;s il prend et mange d&rsquo;autres fruits comme papaye, pasteque, ananas, mandarin, concombre, carotte et haricot.</p>\r\n<p>Ajun aime manger pr&egrave;s du mangeoire.</p>\r\n<p>Mai 2012</p>\r\n<p>Ajun va bien.</p>\r\n<p>Ajun es actif&nbsp;&agrave; se balancer et&nbsp;&agrave; &nbsp;chanter en haut de la cage.</p>\r\n<p>Ajun passe beaucoup de temps en haut de la cage. Il redescend seulement quand il veut prendre ses fruits.</p>\r\n<p>Ajun a bien mang&eacute; ses fruits.</p>\r\n<p>Mars 2011</p>\r\n<p>Ajun va bien sur notre site pour les siamangs et les gibbons de Sumatera qui se trouve sur l\'&icirc;le Marak, a l\'ouest de Padang.</p>','FR'),
	(52734,435,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<div id=\"destText\" class=\"textArea\" style=\"direction: ltr;\">\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Ajun is a male Siamang (<em>Symphalangus syndactylus</em>) who can be found in Sumatera, Indonesia.</p>\r\n<p>The estimate of the Year of birth: 1998.</p>\r\n<p>Ajun was confiscated in Jakarta, the capital of Indonesia. He arrived at Kalaweit Sumatera on 02 December 2010.</p>\r\n<p>The result of the blood test is negative. Ajun is healthy.</p>\r\n<p>Notes :</p>\r\n<p>Supayang Conservation Centre and Sanctuary, Solok, West Sumatera.</p>\r\n<p>June 2018</p>\r\n<p>Ajun is fine. He is active and eats fruit well.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><span><br /></span></div>\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.8458559896264833\">January 2014</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.8776020546378678\">Ajun\'s fine. He\'s active in swinging.</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.3129286594301055\">After balancing, Ajun likes to sit on an extended branch.</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.6471116400011131\">Ajun eats well the fruits and other food as chicken, hard-boiled egg and milk.</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.15042381718060882\">September 2013</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.8228431312828699\">Ajun\'s fine.</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.4823665756852098\">He\'s active in swinging.</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.09358661427168335\">Ajun eats his food well. He always takes and eats bananas first. After it takes and eats other fruits like papaya, watermelon, pineapple, mandarin, cucumber, carrot and bean.</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.8231054570582199\">Ajun likes to eat by the feeder.<br /></span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.4935250844065272\">May 2012</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.64671953295625\">Ajun\'s fine.</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.19553378902781482\">Ajun are active in swinging and singing at the top of the cage.</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.05254520597731582\">Ajun spends a lot of time at the top of the cage. He only comes down when he wants to take his fruit.</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.6410163289552685\">Ajun has good food.</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.735129748386131\">March 2011</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.30401520626176437\">Ajun goes well on our cenre for the siamangs and gibbons of Sumatra which is on the island Marak, west of Padang.</span></div>\r\n</div>','EN'),
