	(53119,540,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<p>Aliya &nbsp;est une femelle gibbon de l&rsquo;esp&egrave;ce <em>Hylobates agilis albibarbis</em>, l&rsquo;une des esp&egrave;ces de gibbons dans le monde qui vit sur l&rsquo;ile Born&eacute;o, Indonesie.</p>\r\n<p>L&rsquo;estimation de l&rsquo;ann&eacute;e de sa naissance&nbsp;: 2014.</p>\r\n<p>Confisqu&eacute;e &agrave;&nbsp;: Palangkaraya, la capitale de Kalimantan Centrale.</p>\r\n<p>Arriv&eacute;e dans Kalaweit Programme&nbsp;: le 04 janvier 2015.</p>\r\n<p>L&rsquo;examen medical: Aliya est infect&eacute;e par hepatite B.</p>\r\n<p>notes :</p>\r\n<p>Pararawen Conservation Centre et Sanctuaire, Muara Teweh, Kalimantan Centrale.</p>\r\n<p>Avril 2018</p>\r\n<p>Aliya va bien. Elle est toujours ensemble avec son compagnon Simon.</p>\r\n<p>Janvier 2017</p>\r\n<p>Aliya et Simon vont bien. Ils sont actifs et mangent bien les fruits.</p>\r\n<p>Aliya eat well the fruits.</p>\r\n<p>Janvier 2016</p>\r\n<p>Aliya et &nbsp;Simon vont bien. Elles passent de temps a jouer ensemble. Ils se poursuivent et s\'attrapent en haut et en bas de la cage.</p>\r\n<p>Ao&ucirc;t 2015</p>\r\n<p>Le 15 ao&ucirc;t 2015, un jour triste pour Aliya et Simon, Obok est d&eacute;ced&eacute;e... Obok est tomb&eacute;e malade...pendant 2 jours elle n&rsquo;a pas &eacute;te active comme d&rsquo;habitude et n&rsquo;a pas bien mang&eacute; les fruits.</p>\r\n<p>L&rsquo;autopsie : l&rsquo;&eacute;quipe v&eacute;t&eacute;rinaire nous a conclu que la cause du d&eacute;c&egrave;s de Obok est par des infections&nbsp; septisemia ( septicaemia ).</p>\r\n<p>Juillet 2015</p>\r\n<p>Aliya est maintenant ensemble avec deux autres jeunes gibbons, Eboc et Simon. Ils s\'entendent bien.</p>\r\n<p>Mars 2015</p>\r\n<p>Aliya va bien. Elle est active et mange bien les fruits.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','FR'),
	(53120,540,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.9018301999058079\">Aliya is a female gibbon of the species Hylobates agilis albibarbis, one of the species of gibbons in the world that lives on Borneo island, Indonesia.</span></div>\r\n<p><span id=\"noHighlight_0.397177912111237\">Estimate year of birth: 2014.</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"noHighlight_0.6533043566990244\">Confiscated at: Palangkaraya, the capital of central Kalimantan.</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"noHighlight_0.46202098867938945\">Arrival in Kalaweit program: January 04, 2015.</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"noHighlight_0.6920660976483838\">Medical examination: Aliya is infected by hepatitis B.</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"noHighlight_0.5360780051529689\">Observations :</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"noHighlight_0.7343181463830991\">Pararawen Conservation Centre and Sanctuary, Muara Teweh, central Kalimantan.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Avril 2018</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Aliya is fine. She is always with her partner Simon.</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"noHighlight_0.352764587542722\">January 2017</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"noHighlight_0.0096340770429435\">Aliya and Simon are fine. They are active and eat the fruit well.</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"noHighlight_0.9025341760669872\">Aliya eat well the fruits.</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"noHighlight_0.5856329786951848\">January 2016</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"noHighlight_0.48249180502869293\">Aliya and Simon are fine. They spend time playing together. They continue and catch themselves up and down the cage.</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"noHighlight_0.8294849995305891\">August 2015</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"noHighlight_0.013690965968406466\">On August 15, 2015, a sad day for Aliya and Simon, Obok has died. Obok felt ill, for 2 days she was not active as usual and did not eat well the fruits.</span></p>\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.8383263061999967\">Autopsy: The veterinary team concluded that the cause of the death of Obok is septisemia infections (septicaemia).</span></div>\r\n<div><span><br /></span></div>\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.3288953106504027\">July 2015</span></div>\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.09183379259800739\">Aliya is now together with two other young Gibbons, Eboc and Simon. They get along well.</span></div>\r\n<div><span><br /></span></div>\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.7089206189898889\">March 2015</span></div>\r\n<div><span id=\"noHighlight_0.9273981555171052\">Aliya\'s fine. It is active and eats the fruit well.</span></div>','EN'),
