	(53156,551,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<p>Aliando est une femelle gibbon de l&rsquo;esp&egrave;ce <em>Hylobates Muelleri muelleri</em>, l&rsquo;une d&rsquo;esp&egrave;ces de gibbons qui vit sur l&rsquo;ile Born&eacute;o, Indonesie.</p>\r\n<p>L&rsquo;estimation de l&rsquo;ann&eacute;e de sa naissance : 2011.</p>\r\n<p>Aliando a &eacute;t&eacute; sauv&eacute;e par le departement forestier de la ville Muara Teweh, Borneo centrale le 06 ao&ucirc;t 2015.</p>\r\n<p>Notes :</p>\r\n<p>Pararawen Conservation Centre et Sanctuaire, Muara Teweh, Borneo centrale.</p>\r\n<p>Mars 2018</p>\r\n<p>Inea et Aliando ont un nouveau membre de la famille. Aliando a donn&eacute; naissance &agrave; un b&eacute;b&eacute; gibbon le 17 mars 2018. Nous appellons le bebe Noela.</p>\r\n<p>Fevrier 2018</p>\r\n<p>Aliando va bien. Elle est toujours ensemble avec son compagnon Inea.</p>\r\n<p>Janvier 2016</p>\r\n<p>Aliando est maintenant avec un autre jeune male gibbon qui s\'appelle Inea.</p>\r\n<p>Elle a du changer de compagnon parceque ses relations avec Gibby ne se sont pas bien entendus.</p>\r\n<p>Decembre 2015</p>\r\n<p>Aliando va bien. Elle est maintenant ensemble avec une autre jeune male gibbon qui s&rsquo;appelle Gibby. Ils s&rsquo;entendent bien.</p>','FR'),
	(53157,551,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<p>Aliando is a female gibbon <em>Hylobates Muelleri muelleri</em>. One&nbsp; gibbon specy who lives in Borneo, Indonesia.</p>\r\n<p>Year of birth (estimation) : 2011</p>\r\n<p>Aliando was rescued in August, 6th 2015 at Muara Teweh, Borneo Centre, by the Forest Departement.</p>\r\n<p>Notes :</p>\r\n<p>Pararawen Conservation Centre and Sanctuary, Muara Teweh, Borneo.</p>\r\n<p>March, 17 2018</p>\r\n<p>Aliando gave birth to a baby gibbon. We called her baby Noela.</p>\r\n<p>February 2018</p>\r\n<p>Aliando and her partner Inea are doing well. They are active and eat well the fruits.</p>\r\n<p>January 2016</p>\r\n<p>Aliando and her new friend Inea are doing well. They are actives and eat well the fruits.</p>\r\n<p>Her relationship with Gibby was not good. So we had to separate Aliando and Gibby to avoid some intimidation. And we put her with another male gibbon more quiet.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>December 2015</p>\r\n<p>Aliando is now with Gibby. For the moment they are just fine.</p>','EN'),
