	(53171,554,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<p><span>Josh est un m&acirc;le&nbsp; gibbon de l&rsquo;esp&egrave;ce&nbsp;<em><span>Hylobates Muelleri muelleri</span></em>, l&rsquo;une d&rsquo;esp&egrave;ces de gibbons qui vit dans le sud de la rivi&egrave;re Mahakam river et &agrave; l&rsquo;ouest de la rivi&egrave;re Barito &agrave; Born&eacute;o, en Indonesie.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>L&rsquo;estimation de l&rsquo;ann&eacute;e de sa naissance : 2009.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Josh&nbsp; a &eacute;t&eacute; sauv&eacute; dans une ville Muara Teweh, Borneo centrale le 02 novembre&nbsp; 2015.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>notes :</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Pararawen Conservation Centre et Sanctuaire, Muara Teweh, Borneo centrale.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Janvier 2018</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Josh va bien. Il est encore seul dans la cage.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Janvier &nbsp;2017</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Josh va bien. Il est actif et mange bien les fruits.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Decembre 2015</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Josh va bien</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Josh est un male&nbsp; gibbon de l&rsquo;esp&egrave;ce&nbsp;<em><span>Hylobates Muelleri muelleri</span></em>, l&rsquo;une d&rsquo;esp&egrave;ces de gibbons qui vit sur l&rsquo;ile Born&eacute;o, Indonesie.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>L&rsquo;estimation de l&rsquo;ann&eacute;e de sa naissance : 2009.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Josh&nbsp; a &eacute;t&eacute; sauv&eacute; dans une ville Muara Teweh, Borneo centrale le 02 novembre&nbsp; 2015.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>notes :</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Pararawen Conservation Centre et Sanctuaire, Muara Teweh, Borneo centrale.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Decembre 2015</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Josh va bien.</span></p>','FR'),
	(53172,554,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<p>Josh is a male gibbon of species <em>Hylobates muelleri muelleri</em>, one of gibbon species who live in the south of Mahakam river and in the west of Barito river in Borneo, Indonesia.</p>\r\n<p>Estimation of his birth year : 2009.</p>\r\n<p>Josh was saved in Muara Teweh&nbsp; in november, 2 2015.</p>\r\n<p>Like many others wild animal, Josh was captured in the forest. For years, He live like a pet with human.</p>\r\n<p>Now with Kalaweit, Josh have a chance to live with others gibbons and to be free again in the forest. But for this, Josh must wait some years of rehabilitation in our center.</p>\r\n<p>Notes :</p>\r\n<p>Pararawen Conservation Center and Santuary, Muara Teweh, Kalimantan Central.</p>\r\n<p>January 2018</p>\r\n<p>Josh is fine. He is active and eat well the fruits.</p>','EN'),
