	(53229,569,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<p>Kinoy is a female gibbon of <em>Hylobates Muelleri muelleri</em>, one of gibbons species who can be found in Kalimantan, Indonesia.</p>\r\n<p>Estimation of her birth year : 2000.</p>\r\n<p>Kinoy was saved in Palangkaraya on july, 23 2015.</p>\r\n<p>Like many others wild animal, Kinoy was captured in the wild. Then she lived with human as a pet.</p>\r\n<p>Notes :</p>\r\n<p>Pararawen Conservation Center and Santuary, Muara Teweh, Central Kalimantan.</p>\r\n<p>May 2018</p>\r\n<p>Kinoy is fine. She is active and eat well the fruits.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','EN'),
