	(53313,592,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<p><span>Momo est une femelle gibbon de l&rsquo;esp&egrave;ce&nbsp;<em><span>Hylobates Agilis albibarbis</span></em>, l&rsquo;une des esp&egrave;ces de gibbon qui vit dans le sud de la rivi&egrave;re Kapuas et &agrave; l&rsquo;ouest de la rivi&egrave;re Barito &agrave; Borneo en Indonesie.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>L&rsquo;estimation de l&rsquo;ann&eacute;e de sa naissance : 2010.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Momo est sauv&eacute;e le 22 juillet 2016 &agrave; Muara Teweh, dans le centre de Borneo.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>L&rsquo;examan d&rsquo;une prise de sang : Momo est saine.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>L&rsquo;histore de Momo</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Momo a vecu depuis tout&nbsp; petit avec l&rsquo;homme. Elle est trait&eacute;e comme un animal de compagnie.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Maintenant elle est avec Kalaweit. Momo a de la chance d&rsquo;&ecirc;tre rel&acirc;ch&eacute; dans la for&ecirc;t. Mais elle d&rsquo;abord passer quelques ann&eacute;es de r&eacute;habilitation dans notre centre.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Notes :</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Pararawen Conservation Centre et Sanctuaire, Muara Teweh, Borneo.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Avril 2018</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Momo va bien. Elle est toujours ensemble avec son compagnon Bob. Ils sont actifs et mangent bien les fruits.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Janvier 2017</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Momo va bien. Elle est maintenant ensemble avec un jeune male gibbon qui s&rsquo;appelle Bob.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Ils s&rsquo;entendent bien.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>','FR'),
	(53314,592,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<p>Momo is a female gibbon of species <em>Hylobates Agilis albibarbis</em>, one of the gibbon species who lives in the south of the Kapuas river and west of the Barito river in Kalimantan, Indonesia.</p>\r\n<p>Year of her birth : 2010.</p>\r\n<p>The result of blood test : Momo is clean.</p>\r\n<p>Momo story :</p>\r\n<p>As many others wild animals, Momo was the victim of deforestation and wild animals trafficking.</p>\r\n<p>Far away from her home and family, Momo has unfortunately been kept as a pet, in a house with humans.</p>\r\n<p>July, 22 2016, Kalaweit succeded in saving Momo in Muara Teweh.</p>\r\n<p>Now at Kalaweit, Momo have a chance to be released in the forest one day. But before that she must spend some rehabilitation steps in our center.</p>\r\n<p>notes :</p>\r\n<p>Pararawen Conservation Center and Sanctuary, Muara Teweh, Kalimantan.</p>\r\n<p>Avril 2018</p>\r\n<p>Momo is fine. She is always with her partner Bob. They are actives and eat well the fruits.</p>\r\n<p>January 2017</p>\r\n<p>Momo is now with a male gibbon name Bob. They are both doing well.</p>','EN'),
