	(53323,595,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<p>Upat est une femelle gibbon qui appartient &agrave; l&rsquo;esp&egrave;ce&nbsp;<em>Hylobates muelleri muelleri</em>, l&rsquo;une des esp&egrave;ces des gibbons qui vit au sud &ndash; est de la rivi&egrave;re Mahakam et &agrave; l&rsquo;ouest de la rivi&egrave;re Barito &agrave; Born&eacute;o en Indon&eacute;sie.</p>\r\n<p>L&rsquo;estimation de l&rsquo;ann&eacute;e de sa naissance : 2014.</p>\r\n<p>Upat a &eacute;t&eacute; sauv&eacute;e dans un village &agrave; Puruk Cahu, Born&eacute;o Centre,&nbsp; le 27 octobre 2016.</p>\r\n<p>L&rsquo;histoire :</p>\r\n<p>Les gens ont s&ucirc;rement tu&eacute; sa maman pour prendre Upat conmme un animal de compagnie. Un b&eacute;b&eacute; gibbon s&rsquo;attache beaucoup &agrave; sa maman. Nous, l&rsquo;homme, ne s&rsquo;imaginons jamais la peur ou la terreur qu&rsquo;Upat a subi &agrave; cause de cette mauvaise experience dans sa vie.</p>\r\n<p>Centre de r&eacute;habilitation :</p>\r\n<p>Pararawen Conservation Centre et Sanctuaire, Muara Teweh, Born&eacute;o Centre.</p>\r\n<p>Avril 2018</p>\r\n<p>Upat et Bombo vont bien. Elles sont active et mangent bien les fruits.</p>\r\n<p>Mars 2017</p>\r\n<p>Upat est maintenant ensemble dans une cage avec un autre jeune femelle gibbon qui s&rsquo;appelle Bombo. Elles s&rsquo;entendent bien.</p>\r\n<p>Janvier 2017</p>\r\n<p>Upat va bien. Elle est active et mange bien les fruits.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>','FR'),
	(53324,595,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<p>Upat is a female gibbon <em>Hylobates muelleri muelleri</em>, one of gibbons species that can be found in southeast of the Mahalam river and west of the Barito river in Kalimantan, Indonesia.</p>\r\n<p>Year of birth (estimation) : 2014.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>History :</p>\r\n<p>When people want to capture a baby gibbon, they must kill his mother. Because during the first years of his life the baby stay grabbed to his mother. The father will die also, because alone he no longer will be able to protect his territory, then not able to find food.</p>\r\n<p>Humans don&rsquo;t realize that it\'s crual to keep a gibbon at home as a pet...</p>\r\n<p>Now at Kalaweit, Upat has a chance to go back again in the forest. But before that, she must spend some years of rehabilitation in our center.</p>\r\n<p>Notes :</p>\r\n<p>Pararawen Conservation Center and Sanctuary, Muara Teweh, Kalimantan central.</p>\r\n<p>Avril 2018</p>\r\n<p>Upat and Bombo are doing well. They are active and eat well the fruits.</p>\r\n<p>March 2017</p>\r\n<p>Upat is now with another young female gibbon name Bombo. They are just fine.</p>\r\n<p>January 2017</p>\r\n<p>Upat is doing well. For a moment she is alone in her aviary.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','EN'),
