	(53348,602,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<p><span>Tom est un m&acirc;le siamang (&nbsp;<em><span>Symphalangus syndactylus</span></em>&nbsp;), l&rsquo;une des esp&egrave;ces de gibbons qui vit sur l&rsquo;&icirc;le Sumatera en Indon&eacute;sie.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>L&rsquo;estimation de l&rsquo;ann&eacute;e de sa naissance : 2012.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>L&rsquo;histoire :</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Tom a &eacute;t&eacute; sauv&eacute; le 06 decembre 2016 &agrave; Jakarta.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Comme beaucoup d&rsquo;autres siamangs et gibbons dans notre centre de rehabilitation, Tom a de la chance d&rsquo;&ecirc;tre rel&acirc;ch&eacute; dans la for&ecirc;t. Pour arriver &agrave; ce but, Tom doit passer quelques &eacute;tapes de rehabilitation qui peuvent prendre des ann&eacute;es.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Notes :</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Supayang Conservation Centre et Sanctuaire, Solok, &agrave; l&rsquo;ouest de Sumatera.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Juin 2018</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Tom va bien. Il est toujours ensemble avec sa compagne Deasy.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Janvier 2018</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Ce mois nous avons plac&eacute;s Tom et Deasy dans une m&ecirc;me cage. C&rsquo;&eacute;tait Deasy qui s&rsquo;approche beaucoup de Tom. Au debut Tom a refus&eacute; Deasy. Il l&rsquo;a frapp&eacute;e ou s&rsquo;est &eacute;loign&eacute; quand Deasy s&rsquo;approche.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Apr&egrave;s quelques heures de tentatives, Tom accepte Deasy. Ils se sont accoupl&eacute;s.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Tom et Deasy &nbsp;sont actifs &agrave; se balancer et &agrave; chanter avec les autres siamangs et gibbons.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Dans le matin, apr&egrave;s avoir chant&eacute;, Tom et Deasy passent de temps &agrave; prendre des bains de soleil et &agrave; chercher des insectes.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Tom et Deasy mangent bien les fruits.</span></p>','FR'),
	(53349,602,'DETAIL','HTML','2018-10-21 05:27:19',NULL,NULL,'<p>Tom is a male siamang <em>Symphalangus Syndactylus</em>, one of gibbons species who can be found in Sumatera, Indonesia.</p>\r\n<p>Estimation of his birth year : 2012.</p>\r\n<p>History :</p>\r\n<p>Tom was saved in Jakarta, Java, on December, 6<sup>th</sup> 2016.</p>\r\n<p>Like many others wild animal, Tom was victim of animal trafficking. He sold in the black market as a pet.</p>\r\n<p>Now with Kalaweit, he live with others siamangs and have less stress.</p>\r\n<p>Notes :</p>\r\n<p>Supayang Conservation Center and Santuary, Solok, West Sumatera.</p>\r\n<p>June 2018</p>\r\n<p>Tom is doing well. He is always with his partner Deasy.</p>\r\n<p>January 2018</p>\r\n<p>Tom is now with a female siamang name Deasy.</p>\r\n<p>Deasy approach a lot Tom but Tom doesn&rsquo;t like when Deasy came closer.</p>\r\n<p>A few hours later, Tom and Deasy become more friendly. They mate.</p>','EN'),
